snippet.textDisplay:
You have messed up Kevin. After years of binging these shows, hoping that they’ll one day be praised on the big screen, and cast and crew working their tails off for the sake of our faithful fandom, you just state that the Marvel TV Shows...
(the same ones who have had Tie-Ins, References, and Respectful consideration to your empire) are no longer canon?
All of that for nothing? Now all the cast and crew can say is “wow, thanks for the opportunity, sucks I didn’t cut it, but I can smile the pain away.”
Daredevil, The Punisher, Jessica Jones, Luke Cage, Agents of S.H.I.E.LD., Runaways, Cloak and Dagger, Iron Fist, and Agent Carter were shows that hit all kinds of audiences in ways you apparently don’t comprehend. If you did, you’d know they don’t deserve this treatment.
I get Jeph had his flaws, as did his works, but when you literally state multiple times that they’re all in the same continuity, then just pull the rug from under, you’re only showing truth on how your word is false. There is time to change this.
Please, the future of your franchise, your position, and your fandom depends on it...
